#1 <s>As an introverted creative entrepreneur who is very privacy-conscious, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but it often does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to be outgoing when dealing with large (evil) tech companies. Advertise here according to the algorithm, share your personal charm. Get verified on that service, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Video, video, still video.
#2 <s>1/3
#3 <s>This year has been a year of transformation for me.
#4 <s>I no longer want to dedicate my money, data, and energy to large tech companies, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only apply a one-size-fits-all outgoing solution to everyone. I am exploring new business models while also working to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by doing things in a certain way.
#5 <s>Wish me luck!
Step one has been taken.
I have exited Facebook, deleted all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and signed out of my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also deleted the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics - and felt great about it.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will be migrating my business over in the coming weeks.
I moved the MX records to Proton, now having full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
